Noma Gigaba was arrested on Friday for alleged domestic violence, assault, malicious damage to property, and crimen injuria. JOHANNESBURG - Former Finance Minister Malusi Gigaba's wife, Nomachule, has been released on bail. Her attorney, Victor Nkwashu, confirmed her release on Saturday night. "She was released on bail of R 5, 000 with condition that she should appear in court on Monday", said Nkwatshu. READ: Why the Hawks made the Noma Gigaba arrest Noma was arrested on Friday for alleged domestic violence, assault, malicious damage to property, and crimen injuria. A video of a damaged car, believed to be her husband's, recently went viral on social media. She is expected to appear in the Hatfield Magistrate court for a bail application on Monday.